### VS Code REST Client Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@speakerName = Target Speaker 1

### ------------------------------------------------------------------------
### General Endpoints
### ------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Check Service Root & Current Dynamic Configuration
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Discover All SoundTouch Speakers on the Local Network
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/discover

### ------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Schedules API
### ------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Get All Schedules
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/schedules

### Add or Update a Schedule
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/schedules
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test Routine",
    "days": [
        "monday",
        "tuesday",
        "wednesday",
        "thursday",
        "friday"
    ],
    "on_time": "08:00",
    "off_time": "09:00",
    "preset": 3,
    "volume": 15
}

### Delete a Schedule
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/schedules/Test Routine

### ------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Speaker-Specific Endpoints
### (Requires speaker to be present and successfully discovered over mDNS)
### ------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Get Current Status of the Speaker
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/status

### Toggle Power State
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/power

### Set Volume to 20%
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/volume
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "volume": 20
}

### Play Preset 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/preset/1

### Play Preset 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{speakerName}}/preset/2
